version_description: Should print out on one page. Tune guitar to 430 for the 'Live' versions accurate, acoustic sound. A great song to practice picking and rhythm. This is the way I like to play it, enjoy.
Neatly formatted, accurate chords with correct bass notes, includes chord legend.
Contains Emadd9 chord (important to the sound of the guitar) as well as chord fingerings and notes on specific ways to play each chord.
There is a flaw on each of the chorded versions of this song.
There are a few differences between chords.

There are 3 chord tabs for this song. One is very poor, the other two are accurate but have very simple beginner chords. After playing repeatedly this song, listening repeatedly to various live/acoustic versions and covers, I came to the conclusion that it has some beautiful transitions and plays which can be transposed acoustically rather nicely. This tab does not give detailed indication on the plays, but when you see the transition chords and listen to the song, they should feet immediately into place.
Completed and corrected chords from other versions. This version is for acoustic guitar tuned a whole step down (standard D tuning).
It's based to the studio version, chords are exactly alike https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GBpbWEpGORM.
Better chords, right timing, precise lyrics.
